&lt;p&gt;This is a hands-on role with real ownership and responsibilities. You’ll be directly responsible for the numbers and continuously building processes to help scale. The right candidate is technically strong, detail-oriented, and comfortable operating with the independence that comes with being the owner of the accounting function.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review and oversee the external accounting team (e.g., AR/AP and month-end close functions) - ensuring accuracy and accountability to timelines and quality&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare and post all adjusting journal entries, accruals, and non-routine entries that fall outside the external team’s scope; own general ledger and chart of accounts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the full month-end close process - coordinating with the external team, completing internal entries, and ensuring books are closed accurately and on time&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare monthly, quarterly, and annual financial statements (P&amp;amp;L, balance sheet, cash flow) and deliver clean reporting packages to leadership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain SaaS and ARR reporting - tracking subscription revenue, churn, and recurring revenue metrics in line with ASC 606 revenue recognition standards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own payroll processing and reconciliation - ensuring timely and accurate payroll runs and proper recording of payroll liabilities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage banking relationships, cash positioning, and daily treasury operations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the annual audit and tax preparation process, serving as the primary liaison with external auditors and tax advisors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own our accounting systems (QuickBooks and integrated tools) - ensuring data integrity, clean integrations, and a well-maintained tech stack&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and implement process improvements that strengthen controls and increase efficiency across the accounting function&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
